Description: Fragment of round handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff.
Production date: 139 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Name Lapheides. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 188a, 9. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0167.43.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1002)
